  "text": "where p u = X (x 1 u ) and p u = X(x 2 u ) are the posterior mean projections of STs x 1 u and x 2 u from trees x 1 and x 2 , respectively. To demonstrate that the weight function T ( p, p ) in (10) is a kernel (and so is k am−gtm ), we can exploit the definition of Wedland functions [CITATION_1] that are a family of piecewise polynomial covariance functions with compact support. A simple family of Wendland functions is that based on univariate polynomials, it is characterized by positive definiteness on R d with support on the unitary compact. Among the members of this family, we are interested in the following Wendland function:",
